        "text": "The document page is from Section 11 of the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, focusing on data acquisition and aggregation. It outlines procedures for handling different types of data:\n\n1. **ERCOT Read ESI ID Data Extract**:\n   - Selects all ERCOT read ESI IDs for market participants.\n   - Provides interval data for each channel associated with an ESI ID.\n\n2. **Treatment of ERCOT Polled Settlement Resource ID Data**:\n   - ERCOT is identified as the MRE (Meter Reading Entity).\n   - Models and populates data to ensure netting and aggregation conform to ERCOT Protocols.\n   - Makes RID interval and SCADA data available to relevant entities.\n   - The data extract selects all ERCOT read RIDs for market participants and provides interval data for each channel.\n   - Provides interval data to TSPs/DSPs by noon on the tenth business day after reading the EPS meter.\n   - Updates revised data to TSP/DSP by noon of the tenth business day after any edits.\n\n3. **Treatment of ERCOT-Polled Settlement Energy Storage Resource Load Data**:\n   - For WSL and Non-WSL ESR Charging Load, ERCOT is identified as the MRE.\n   - Models and populates data to ensure netting and aggregation conform to ERCOT Protocols.",
