        "id": "0bbb0651-19f5-4690-9cb2-ce4e1530f83f",
        "score": 0.6424182,
        "text": "The document outlines procedures for the Electric Reliability Council of Texas (ERCOT) regarding topology and model verification, and the submission of declarations for natural gas pipeline coordination.\n\n### Topology and Model Verification\n1. **Notification and Verification**: ERCOT must notify the appropriate Transmission Service Provider (TSP) or Resource Entity about constraints identified in the evaluation of chronic congestion. The TSP or Resource Entity must verify the accuracy of data in the Network Operations Model and Updated Network Model, including transmission facility ratings.\n\n2. **System Implementation Conditions**: A note specifies conditions under which Southern Cross must provide funds and sign an interconnection agreement with a TSP. The TSP must then notify ERCOT about the construction and financial security for the interconnection.\n\n3. **Inaccuracies and Coordination**: If inaccuracies are found in the models or facility configuration, ERCOT must coordinate with the facility owner to update the ratings as needed.\n\n### Submission of Declarations of Natural Gas Pipeline Coordination\n1. **Declaration Requirement**: Resource Entities using natural gas must submit a declaration to ERCOT, confirming communication with pipeline operators to assess impacts on resource availability during peak load seasons.\n\n2. **Outage Reporting**: If a Resource Entity or its Qualified Scheduling Entity (QSE) knows of any pipeline-related issues affecting resource availability, they must report the outage or derate in the ERCOT Outage Scheduler promptly.",
