        "id": "da9829f9-5976-4bd5-ad2b-306b9dcb56ce",
        "score": 0.6392103,
        "text": "The document outlines management activities for the ERCOT system, focusing on the coordination and registration of various resource entities. Key points include:\n\n1. **Resource Coordination**: ERCOT coordinates with Resource Entities to model and map Load Resources to appropriate loads in the Network Operations Model.\n\n2. **Distribution Generation Resources (DGR) and Energy Storage**: Resource Entities representing DGR or Distribution Energy Storage Resources (DESR) must provide ERCOT and related parties with detailed information and telemetry for registration and mapping in the Network Operations Model.\n\n3. **Settlement Only Distribution Generators (SODG/SODESS)**: These entities must register with ERCOT and provide necessary information for mapping in the Network Operations Model. A note indicates a future replacement of paragraph (4) with updated requirements upon system implementation.\n\n4. **Split Generation Resources**: These resources must provide information for their share of generation to be represented in the Network Operations Model, ensuring connection to the ERCOT Transmission Grid.\n\n5. **DC Tie Resources**: ERCOT will create a DC Tie Resource to represent generation injection into the ERCOT Transmission Grid from DC Ties. \n\nOverall, the document emphasizes the importance of detailed information sharing and coordination for effective resource management within the ERCOT system.",
