        "text": "The document is a section from the ERCOT Nodal Protocols, specifically focusing on management activities for the ERCOT system. It outlines requirements for modeling transmission elements and resources.\n\n1. **Transmission Elements**: \n   - Lists parameters needed for modeling, such as voltage, switching device names, connectivity, nominal voltage, and other necessary data.\n   - ERCOT Operating Guides must include parameters for standard reactor and capacitor switching plans for the Network Operations Model.\n   - ERCOT is responsible for modeling devices and providing copies of switching plans to market participants. Changes in guidelines or plans must be communicated to ERCOT before implementation, except in emergencies.\n\n2. **Modeling of Resources and Transmission Loads**:\n   - Each Resource Entity must provide ERCOT and its interconnecting Transmission Service Provider (TSP) with information about its Generation Resources, SOGs, and Load Resources.\n   - All types of Transmission Generation Resources and other specified generators must be modeled to provide equivalent generation injections to the ERCOT Transmission Grid.\n   - ERCOT coordinates the modeling of resources to ensure consistency between TSP models and ERCOT models.\n\n3. **Implementation Note**:\n   - A note indicates a replacement paragraph for future implementation, detailing similar requirements with slight modifications, including the addition of Settlement Only Transmission Energy Storage Systems (SOTESSs).\n\n4. **Load Resources**:\n   - Resource Entities representing Load Resources or Aggregate Load Resources must provide relevant information to ERCOT and interconnecting Distribution Service Providers (DSPs).",
